			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h1 class="about theme-color" >Women leading the way out of poverty</h1><br>

				<p>The De’ Bridge community center Women’s Empowerment group was launched in 2014 as an initiative to fight poverty at the grassroots level. It was formed by women for women, and is led by women.<br><br>
				At the De’ Bridge community we strongly believe that women are the pillars of the society. We started women group initiative with the primary aim of helping women to be financially independent. The women involved all know first-hand the challenges of raising a family in this environment. As well as providing support, the group helps provide income-generating opportunities. Our initiatives brings women together and enable them to learn social and technical skill to build their small business .In addition from learning from each other, we support them by providing expertise from which they gain skill such as tailoring, baking and small scale farming..</p>

